description: In Bolivia, economic turmoil caused by dependence on the dollar fuels distrust in government and its claim of a ‘failed coup.'
title: Economic turmoil in Bolivia fuels distrust in government and its claim of a 'failed coup'

description: French President Emmanuel Macron suffered a damaging defeat in France's first round of preliminary elections. Macron's centrist alliance came in third place. The far-right national rally party won the election with 33% of the vote. NBC News' Keir Simmons reports on what's next politically for France amid the approaching Olympic games.
title: Far-right party wins first round of French parliamentary election

description: Thousands of Jewish ultra-Orthodox men clashed with Israeli police in central Jerusalem on Sunday during a protest against a Supreme Court order for them to begin enlisting for military service.
title: Ultra-Orthodox protest against order to enlist in Israeli military turns violent in Jerusalem

description: Jewish ultra-Orthodox men clashed with Israeli police in central Jerusalem on Sunday. The protests followed an Israeli Supreme Court order for them to begin enlisting for military service.
title: Jewish ultra-Orthodox men protest Supreme Court ruling on military draft

description: Results from the first round of the French parliamentary elections show a strong lead by the far-right National Rally party. NBC News' Claudio Lavanga reports for Early Today on what may turn out to be a disaster for French President Emmanuel Macron.
title: Far-right National Rally party celebrates big win in first round of French elections

description: Hurricane Beryl is expected to strengthen as it heads toward the southeast Caribbean and then onwards into the Gulf. NBC News meteorologist Michelle Grossman says it's unusual to see such a strong storm for early in hurricane season.
title: Hurricane Beryl packs 120 mph winds as it heads toward the Windward Islands
